org.apache.poi.sl.usermodel

Interface ObjectData

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HSLFObjectData, XSLFObjectData 

    public interface ObjectData
    Common interface for OLE shapes, i.e. shapes linked to embedded documents(OLE形状的通用接口，即链接到嵌入文档的形状)
    Since:
    POI 4.0.0

      • hasDirectoryEntry

        default boolean hasDirectoryEntry()
        Returns:
        does this ObjectData have an associated POIFS Directory Entry? (Not all do, those that don't have a data portion)(此对象数据是否具有关联的POIFS目录条目？(Not所有这些都是，那些没有数据部分的）)

      • getDirectory

        default DirectoryEntry getDirectory()
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Gets the object data. Only call for ones that have data though. See hasDirectoryEntry(). The caller has to close the corresponding POIFSFileSystem(获取对象数据。但仅要求那些拥有数据的人。请参阅hasDirectoryEntry（）。调用者必须关闭相应的POIFSFileSystem)
        Returns:
        the object data as an OLE2 directory.(将对象数据作为MBE 2目录。)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there was an error reading the data.(java.io. IOResponse-如果读取数据时出错。)

      • getOLE2ClassName

        java.lang.String getOLE2ClassName()
        Returns:
        the OLE2 Class Name of the object(对象的MBE 2类名称)

      • getFileName

        java.lang.String getFileName()
        Returns:
        a filename suggestion - inspecting/interpreting the Directory object probably gives a better result(文件名建议-检查/解释目录对象可能会得到更好的结果)
